cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.LG 

The paper deals with image classification using convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and specifically focuses on identifying the source smartphone of document images shared over messaging platforms. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves image processing and multimedia (cs.MM) techniques, as well as potential security and privacy concerns (cs.CR). Finally, the use of machine learning algorithms for classification tasks suggests a connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
